<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-11T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/11–944: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-11T16:00:00-04:00">November
                                    11, 1944, 4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9471. As conveyed by telephone (Matthews to Mosely), the War Department
                            desires to add after the words “may be agreed” the following “hereafter
                            by U.K. and U.S. military authorities (Combined Chiefs of Staff)” in the
                            protocol on zones of occupation. (Deptel 9466).</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>